create new directory in /root and cd directory name
git --version (to check available git version)
git init (to initialize the git at present location and you will see .git hidden file)
git config --global user.email “abc.yz@gmail.com”
git config –global user.name ”johnny”
git remote add origin repositoryurl (to initialize git repository)
git status (to check the status of git)
git add filename (to add/initial a file for git push (indexing)) 
git commit -m "any message" (to initial commit a files for git push (staging))
git push -u origin master (to push files (uploading))
git push
git add -A (to add all files at a time)
git branch name (to create a new branch)
git checkout name (to switch the branch)
git branch (to check available branches)

